$ Excel function: hyperlink

code {
=hyperlink(target)
=hyperlink(target; friendlyName)
code }

{ Calling a VBA function with a hyperlink

  It is possible to call a → development/languages/VBA/functions[VBA function] with a hyperlink by prepending the name of the `target` with a hash symbol (`#`):
code {
=hyperlink("#hyperlinkClick()"; "go")
code }

The function then needs to be declared in a → development/languages/VBA/language/module[VBA module] like so
code {
function hyperlinkClick() as range

   set hyperlinkClick = → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Application/index#excel-application-selection[selection]
   msgBox "clicked

end function
code }

  It is also possible to pass parameters (references, scalars…) to to the function

code {
=hyperlink("#funcWithParam(  a1)"                ; "go")
=hyperlink("#funcWithParam(""hard coded value"")"; "go")
code }

}

sa:

  The → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Hyperlink[`hyperlink`] object.

  → Microsoft/Office/Excel/functions[Excel functions]
